{"word":"γέννημα","slug":"γέννημα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γέννημα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γεννάω'><el>γεννάω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>that which is produced</i> or <i>born, a child</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—any <i>product</i> or <i>work</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>breeding, nature</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>a begetting</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}